Compound words formed from two simple words have merely a hyphen placed between their com- ponent parts.

It should be borne in mind, that the Vocabularies comprise only such words as occur in the works to which they are respectively appended, and take notice of those forces alone in which they therein occur. Hence it will be seen that anything like a philosophical distribution of terms on the plan of a General Dictionary is not possible: At the same time it is to be remarked that the various meanings of the several words found in each Author, are arranged with as close an approach to the sequence of mear» ings as circumstances allow.
